{# templates/roadmaps/forex/demo-to-live.html.twig #}
{% extends 'base-roadmaps.html.twig' %}

{% block stylesheets %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_link_tags('forex_css') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block javascripts %}
    {{ parent() }}
    {{ encore_entry_script_tags('forex_js') }}
{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <div class="container">
        <!-- article hero – forex style -->
        <div class="article-hero animate">
            <div class="hero-content">
                <div class="hero-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-rocket"></i>
                </div>
                <h1>From Demo to Live: <span>When and How to Transition</span></h1>
                <p class="hero-description">
                    Moving from demo to live trading is a huge psychological leap. Learn the signs that you're ready,
                    how to choose the right broker, and how to manage your first real trades without blowing your account.
                </p>
                <div class="phase-tag">
                    <i class="fas fa-layer-group"></i> Phase 4: Skill Building · 8 min read
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- introduction -->
        <section class="animate">
            <h2 class="section-title">🚀 The Final Frontier</h2>
            <p style="font-size: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">
                You've spent weeks or months on a demo account, refining your strategy and building confidence.
                But demo trading is not the same as live trading. Real money changes everything – emotions run higher,
                discipline is tested, and every pip feels personal.
            </p>
            <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--gray-color);">
                This article will help you determine if you're truly ready, guide you through selecting a reputable broker,
                and provide a step‑by‑step plan for your first weeks of live trading. The goal is not just to survive,
                but to build a foundation for long‑term success.
            </p>
        </section>

        <!-- readiness checklist grid -->
        <div class="rule-grid animate">
            <div class="rule-item" style="border-top-color: var(--forex-color);">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Consistent Profits</h3>
                <div class="percentage" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">3+ months</div>
                <p>You've been profitable on demo for at least 3 months, with a positive expectancy and a max drawdown under control.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item" style="border-top-color: var(--forex-color);">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-check-double"></i> Followed Your Plan</h3>
                <div class="percentage" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">90%+ adherence</div>
                <p>You can look back at your journal and see that you followed your entry/exit rules consistently, without emotional deviations.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item" style="border-top-color: var(--forex-color);">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-brain"></i> Emotional Control</h3>
                <div class="percentage" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">No revenge trading</div>
                <p>You've experienced losing streaks on demo and handled them without revenge trading or abandoning your strategy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rule-item" style="border-top-color: var(--forex-color);">
                <h3><i class="fas fa-database"></i> Broker Research</h3>
                <div class="percentage" style="font-size: 1.2rem;">Regulated & trusted</div>
                <p>You've selected a broker that is well‑regulated, has good reviews, and offers the trading conditions you need.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- deeper dive: the transition plan -->
        <div class="card animate">
            <h3 style="font-size: 1.8rem; margin-bottom: 20px;">📋 Your 4‑Step Transition Plan</h3>
            <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">
                Follow these steps to make the switch smoothly.
            </p>
            <div style="background: #f1f5f9; padding: 20px; border-radius: 16px; margin-bottom: 30px;">
                <ol style="list-style-position: inside; line-height: 2;">
                    <li><strong>Start small</strong> – Fund your live account with an amount you can afford to lose (e.g., $500–$1,000). Treat it as a tuition fee.</li>
                    <li><strong>Trade micro lots</strong> – Use the smallest position size possible (0.01 lots). Your goal is to adapt psychologically, not to make money.</li>
                    <li><strong>Stick to your demo plan</strong> – Trade exactly as you did on demo. No changes, no “gut feel” trades.</li>
                    <li><strong>Review weekly</strong> – Compare your live trades to your demo performance. Are emotions affecting your decisions? Adjust if needed.</li>
                </ol>
                <p class="pro-tip" style="margin-top: 15px; background-color: #eef2ff; border-left-color: #3182ce;"><i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i> Many traders fail because they switch strategies or increase size too soon. Keep it boring for the first 50–100 live trades.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- INTERACTIVE TOOL: Demo-to-Live Readiness Checker -->
        <div class="card animate" style="margin: 40px 0;" id="readiness-checker">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-clipboard-check"></i> Demo‑to‑Live Readiness Checker</h3>
            <p>Answer a few questions to see if you're ready to transition.</p>

            <div style="margin: 20px 0;">
                <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                    <label style="display: block; font-weight: 600;">1. How many months have you traded consistently on demo?</label>
                    <select id="q1" class="cat-input" style="width: 100%; max-width: 300px;">
                        <option value="0">Less than 1 month</option>
                        <option value="1">1–2 months</option>
                        <option value="2">3–5 months</option>
                        <option value="3">6+ months</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                    <label style="display: block; font-weight: 600;">2. What is your win rate over the last 50 demo trades?</label>
                    <select id="q2" class="cat-input" style="width: 100%; max-width: 300px;">
                        <option value="0">Below 30%</option>
                        <option value="1">30–40%</option>
                        <option value="2">40–50%</option>
                        <option value="3">Above 50%</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                    <label style="display: block; font-weight: 600;">3. Have you ever revenge traded on demo after a loss?</label>
                    <select id="q3" class="cat-input" style="width: 100%; max-width: 300px;">
                        <option value="0">Yes, often</option>
                        <option value="1">Sometimes</option>
                        <option value="2">Rarely</option>
                        <option value="3">Never</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                    <label style="display: block; font-weight: 600;">4. Do you consistently use stop losses and follow your position sizing rules?</label>
                    <select id="q4" class="cat-input" style="width: 100%; max-width: 300px;">
                        <option value="0">No, I often skip them</option>
                        <option value="1">Sometimes</option>
                        <option value="2">Most of the time</option>
                        <option value="3">Always</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-bottom: 15px;">
                    <label style="display: block; font-weight: 600;">5. Have you researched and chosen a regulated broker for live trading?</label>
                    <select id="q5" class="cat-input" style="width: 100%; max-width: 300px;">
                        <option value="0">No, not yet</option>
                        <option value="1">I've looked but not decided</option>
                        <option value="2">I have a shortlist</option>
                        <option value="3">Yes, I'm ready to fund</option>
                    </select>
                </div>
                <button id="readinessBtn" class="btn-outline" style="margin-top: 10px;">Check Readiness</button>
            </div>

            <div id="readinessResult" style="margin-top: 25px; padding: 15px; background: var(--light-color); border-radius: 12px; font-size: 1.2rem; text-align: center;">
                Your readiness score will appear here.
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- example trade box -->
        <div class="highlight-box animate">
            <h3><i class="fas fa-bolt"></i> Example – Maria’s First Live Trade</h3>
            <p>Maria had 4 months of profitable demo trading with a 55% win rate. She funded her live account with $500 and traded 0.01 lots (micro). Her first trade was a long EUR/USD setup she had taken many times on demo. It hit its 20‑pip stop loss, and she lost $2. She felt a pang of regret but reminded herself: “This is why I start small.” She stuck to her plan and ended the month with a small profit – but more importantly, she proved she could handle the emotions.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- pro tip: the psychological shift -->
        <div class="pro-tip animate" style="background-color: #fff5f0; border-left-color: #ff6b35;">
            <h4 style="margin-top: 0;"><i class="fas fa-heartbeat" style="color:#ff6b35;"></i> The Real Money Effect</h4>
            <p>Even the most disciplined demo trader can freeze up when real money is on the line. Your heart will pound, your palms will sweat. This is normal. <strong>The key is to trade through it with small size until your brain realizes that a $2 loss is not a threat to your survival.</strong></p>
        </div>

        <!-- quiz section (conditional) -->
        {% if app.user and quiz is defined and quiz %}
            {# Logged in user – quiz already taken #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">🧠 You've already taken this quiz</h3>
                <p style="color: #e2e8f0; font-size: 1.2rem;">
                    Your score: <strong>{{ quiz.quizzScore }}%</strong>
                </p>
                <p style="color: #cbd5e0;">
                    You can retake the quiz to improve your score. Click the button below to reset it.
                </p>
                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: page.journey.name, slug: slug, retake: 1 }) }}"
                       class="btn"
                       style="background-color: #ff6b35; color: white; text-decoration: none;">
                        Retake Quiz
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        {% else %}
            {# Show quiz (interactivity blocked by JS if not logged in) #}
            <div class="quiz-container animate" data-page-id="{{ page.id }}">
                <h3 style="color:white; margin-top: 0;">📝 Test your knowledge: Demo to Live Transition</h3>

                <div class="quiz-question">1. How long should you ideally be profitable on demo before going live?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="1">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">1 week</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">1 month</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">At least 3 months</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">No need, just go for it</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">2. What position size should you start with on a live account?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="2">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Standard lots (1.0)</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Mini lots (0.1)</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Micro lots (0.01) or smallest possible</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Whatever you used on demo</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">3. Why is it important to trade the same strategy live as you did on demo?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="3">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">To save time</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">To isolate the psychological impact, not change variables</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Because the broker requires it</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Demo strategies don't work live</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">4. What should you do if you experience a losing streak on live?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="4">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Double your size to recover faster</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Stick to your plan, review your journal, and ensure you're following rules</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Switch to a new strategy immediately</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Stop trading forever</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-question">5. Which factor is most important when choosing a live broker?</div>
                <div class="quiz-options" data-question="5">
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Highest leverage</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="correct">Strong regulation and good reviews</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Lowest minimum deposit</div>
                    <div class="quiz-option" data-answer="wrong">Number of currency pairs</div>
                </div>

                <div class="quiz-actions">
                    <button id="quiz-submit" class="btn">Get score & submit</button>
                </div>
                <div class="quiz-result"></div>
            </div>
        {% endif %}

        <!-- next steps in phase 4 (skill building) -->
        <section style="margin: 60px 0;">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="text-align: center;">📘 Continue building your skills</h2>
            <div class="next-steps">
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'forex', slug: 'fundamental-analysis-central-banks' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-university"></i>
                    <h3>Fundamental Analysis</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--gray-color);">Central banks and economic data.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'forex', slug: 'developing-trading-strategy' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-cogs"></i>
                    <h3>Developing a Trading Strategy</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--gray-color);">Combine rules into a plan.</p>
                </a>
                <a href="{{ path('app_page_show', { journey: 'forex', slug: 'advanced-risk-management' }) }}" class="next-card">
                    <i class="fas fa-link"></i>
                    <h3>Advanced Risk Management</h3>
                    <p style="color: var(--gray-color);">Hedging and correlations.</p>
                </a>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>
{% endblock %}
